I started this course: https://www.coursera.org/learn/introduction-programming-unity but did not complete it, despite finishing 80% of the modules. I thought it was slightly below my skill level in terms of programming concepts (it was aimed at people who have never programmed before). It was also difficult to motivate myself without a cohort to work towards a goal with.

There are loads of indie game developers that I really admire. I love Lucus Pope's games (I'm not sure if you would consider him a one person tech company!), as well as Concerned Ape - the person behind Stardew Valley. Whenever I come across a small team of game devs that have managed to make an amazing game with very few resources, it just really makes me want to do the something similar. Whilst precarious, small studios are a great antidote to crunch and big budget production environments.
